# ================================================================================
# This Area Of Code Is: Git Ignore File
# Explanation: Tells Git which files/folders to NOT track in version control.
# Prevents sensitive data (API keys, node_modules) and temporary files from
# being uploaded to GitHub.
# In Other Words: The "do not save" list for Git - keeps secrets and junk out.
# ================================================================================

# This Area Of Code Is: Node.js Dependencies
# Explanation: The node_modules folder contains thousands of downloaded packages.
# These should be installed locally, not committed to Git.
# In Other Words: Don't upload the downloaded tools folder - everyone can install their own.
node_modules/

# This Area Of Code Is: Environment Variables
# Explanation: .env files contain secret API keys and passwords. Never commit these!
# In Other Words: Keep secrets like API keys out of GitHub.
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local

# This Area Of Code Is: macOS System Files
# Explanation: macOS creates these hidden files for folder settings. Not needed in the project.
# In Other Words: Mac computer junk files - ignore them.
.DS_Store
.AppleDouble
.LSOverride

# This Area Of Code Is: Log Files
# Explanation: Log files are generated during runtime and don't need to be saved.
# In Other Words: Ignore debug log files.
*.log
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*

# This Area Of Code Is: Editor Files
# Explanation: Temporary files created by text editors and IDEs.
# In Other Words: Files created by coding programs while you work.
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# This Area Of Code Is: Build Output
# Explanation: Compiled/built files that are generated from source code.
# In Other Words: Files created when building the app - they'll be regenerated.
dist/
build/
.cache/

# This Area Of Code Is: Firebase Cache
# Explanation: Local Firebase emulator and cache files.
# In Other Words: Firebase's temporary local files.
.firebase/
